      "raw_text": "branch of the Inland stops at that\nplace, but right of way has been\nsecured and surveyed for some dis\nlance south. The o. r. & N. is anx-\nious to head off the Graves inter-\nests, and 1t is developing into an\nother tilt between the Hill and Har-\nriman forces, represented by the\nrival lines.\n\n\nBids have been asked by the city\nsinking fund commission for the\n100000 issue of water extension\nbonds recently authorized by the\ncity council to carry on the addi-\nlions to the water plant now under\nway. Corporation Counsel Conner\nhas ruled that this amount of bonds\ncan be issued without a special\nelection.\n\n\nIt has been definitely learned\nthat the Milwaukee will have a con-\nnection between Occur d'Alene and\nSpokane, as the line between the\ntwo cities has been surveyed, prac-\ntically paralleling the Inland."
